&lt;p&gt;We are gathering a team of enthusiastic and experienced professionals to help develop the Bee U CYP ASC/ NeurodevelopmentalPathway. The ASC practitioner posts will join our existing Multi-Disciplinary team of professionals, headed by the General Manager, Operational Leads, Clinical Leads, and in developing our Service (recently renamed ‘Bee U’ by local young people). The Bee U service is a partnership between Midland Partnership Foundation Trust, The Children’s Society, Kooth and Healios working together in the interests of children and young people in Shropshire and Telford &amp; Wrekin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be scope for creativity in this team, to develop evidence based diagnosticassessments, to be informed by the local Transformation Plan, Future in Mind and the THRIVE framework. It really is time to think differently and creatively about how we can help more children and young people with their emotional wellbeing and mental health. You will be supported by professionals in all parts of our service and the wider partnership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Amy Morris on 0300 124 0093&lt;/p&gt;
